# Menhausen landing — SEO development rules

## Architecture

- **Stack:** React SPA (`wouter`) built with Vite, deployed to **GitHub Pages** behind **Cloudflare**.
- **Crawlers** receive static HTML from **build-time prerender** (`scripts/prerender.mjs`), not the empty JS shell.
- **Route list** is defined once in [`scripts/routes.mjs`](../../scripts/routes.mjs) (static routes + slugs parsed from data files).

## Adding a new page or route

1. Add the route in [`client/src/App.tsx`](../../client/src/App.tsx).
2. If the route is dynamic, add a `slug` to the appropriate data file under `client/src/lib/`.
3. Add the static path to `STATIC_ROUTES` in [`scripts/routes.mjs`](../../scripts/routes.mjs) if it is not derived from data slugs.
4. Run `npm run generate:sitemap` (or full `npm run build:client`) so [`client/public/sitemap.xml`](../../client/public/sitemap.xml) stays in sync.
5. Verify prerender output: `dist/<path>.html` (or `dist/index.html` for `/`) must exist and return **200** on GitHub Pages without a trailing-slash redirect.

## Every page must have

- Exactly **one** descriptive `<h1>` (visible, not `sr-only` only).
- The [`<SEO>`](../../client/src/components/seo.tsx) component with `title` (≥ 20 chars with brand suffix), `description`, and `canonical`.
- Meaningful body content in the prerendered HTML (not an empty `#root`).

## Images

Every `<img>` must include:

- `alt` — descriptive text, or `alt=""` for decorative tracking pixels only.
- `width` and `height` — intrinsic dimensions to prevent layout shift.

Prefer [`AnchorIcon`](../../client/src/components/anchor-icon.tsx) for the logo mark.

## Internal linking

- List/index pages must link to **every** detail page (techniques, professions, compare, blog).
- Detail pages should link back to their index and to 1–2 related sections (techniques ↔ professions ↔ stress-test).
- Nav and footer links live in [`client/src/components/layout.tsx`](../../client/src/components/layout.tsx); keep them updated.

## Security headers

- GitHub Pages cannot set response headers; use **Cloudflare** (see [`docs/seo-security-headers.md`](../../docs/seo-security-headers.md)).
- Keep the CSP meta tag in [`client/index.html`](../../client/index.html) aligned with Cloudflare rules.
- When adding a new third-party origin (analytics, fonts, APIs), update **both** CSP locations.

## Build & deploy checklist

Before merging landing changes:

```bash
npm run build:client
```

Confirm:

- [ ] `dist/<route>.html` exists for all routes in `scripts/routes.mjs` (`dist/index.html` for `/`)
- [ ] Each prerendered page has unique `<title>`, one `<h1>`, and internal `<a href="/...">` links
- [ ] `client/public/sitemap.xml` includes all public routes
- [ ] No new `<img>` without `alt` + `width` + `height`
- [ ] Asset filenames under `dist/assets/` contain no underscores (Vite plugin renames them)

## Do not

- Rely on client-only `document.title` / meta updates for SEO — prerender must capture them.
- Add routes to `sitemap.xml` manually without updating `scripts/routes.mjs`.
- Remove the prerender step from CI ([`.github/workflows/deploy.yml`](../../.github/workflows/deploy.yml)).
- Overwrite `dist/index.html` during prerender before all routes are captured (prerender buffers output in memory).
